<p>The color of the meat samples coated by CLEO‐loaded PMSM was measured by means of a digital Chroma meter (Konica Minolta, CR‐400, Japan). The device was firstly calibrated by a white tile standard, and the color indices (
 <italic>L</italic>*, 
 <italic>b</italic>*, and 
 <italic>a</italic>*) and total color difference (Δ
 <italic>E</italic>) of the samples were then measured by the instrument (Realini et al., 
 <xref rid="fsn32137-bib-0055" ref-type="ref">2017</xref>):
 <disp-formula id="fsn32137-disp-0004">
  <math id="nlm-math-4">
   <mrow>
    <mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi>
    <mi>E</mi>
    <mo>=</mo>
    <msqrt>
     <mrow>
      <msup>
       <mrow>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi>
        <mi>L</mi>
        <mo>∗</mo>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
       </mrow>
       <mn>2</mn>
      </msup>
      <mo>+</mo>
      <msup>
       <mrow>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi>
        <mi>b</mi>
        <mo>∗</mo>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
       </mrow>
       <mn>2</mn>
      </msup>
      <mo>+</mo>
      <msup>
       <mrow>
        <mo stretchy="false">(</mo>
        <mi mathvariant="normal">Δ</mi>
        <mi>a</mi>
        <mo>∗</mo>
        <mo stretchy="false">)</mo>
       </mrow>
       <mn>2</mn>
      </msup>
     </mrow>
    </msqrt>
   </mrow>
  </math>
 </disp-formula>
</p>
